WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified body profile for Fujifilm GFX series medium-format and X-series
cameras using F-Log2 encoding. It contains the exact mathematical IDT (Input
Device Transform), F-Log2 and F-Log2 C curve parameters with their inverses,
native color space primaries (Rec.2020), white balance presets, ISO sensitivity
ranges, and sensor metrology data. This is the single source of truth for
linearizing Fujifilm F-Log2 footage to scene-referred ACES2065-1.

WHY IT EXISTS
Fujifilm’s F-Log2 preserves over 14 stops of dynamic range using a log base-2
curve and Rec.2020 gamut. Integrating GFX or X-H2S footage into an ACES or GIOP
pipeline requires an exact, verified inverse transform. Without this certified
body file, the unique F-Log2 encoding can be misinterpreted (e.g., confused
with F-Log v1), leading to color shifts and highlight errors. This file
provides the mathematically auditable IDT, eliminating guesswork.

HOW IT WORKS
The file defines the transform chain:
  1. Inverse F-Log2 (log base‑2, with certified constants) → linear Rec.2020 RGB.
     If F-Log2 C (extended color) is active, a slightly wider gamut is assumed;
     the inverse curve remains the same.
  2. Rec.2020 to ACES2065‑1 matrix (3×3, D65‑to‑D60 adaptation).
  3. White balance gain inverse (as-shot or preset).
All constants are provided for both medium-format (GFX100 II) and APS-C
(X-H2S) models, as F-Log2 is sensor‑size agnostic.

